  "text": "Simpson's diversity [CITATION_1] was used to summarize the evenness of taxa across indicator classes. Evenness considered the entire range of indicator scores and, additionally, the lower and upper limits (i.e., the evenness of the four sequential indicator classes representing the respectively highest and lowest indicator ranks).",
